Chilean Stocks: Banco Santander Chile, Lan Airlines and Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-12-06T20:54:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/chilean-stocks-banco-santander-chile-lan-airlines-and-vapores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index fell 0.2 percent to 4,092.23. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index rose 0.2 percent to 2,240.58.  Banco Santander Chile (BSAN)   rose 3.4 percent to 33.39
pesos. Spain’s Banco Santander SA ended today the book building
process for the sale of a 7.8 percent stake in Santander Chile,
the country’s largest lender. Allocation of shares is scheduled
for tomorrow.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES)   retreated 3.7
percent to 113.58 pesos. Latin America’s largest container
shipping company valued its port services unit Sudamericana
Agencias Aereas & Maritimas SA at $520 million, according to a
statement posted yesterday on the company’s website. CSAV plans
to combine its unit with Royal Boskalis Westminster NV’s SMIT
unit to create a $990 million joint venture.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   advanced 0.7 percent to 12,251
pesos, its second day of gains. An attorney at Brazil’s
antitrust regulator Cade said yesterday the entity should
approve Lan’s takeover of Tam SA without restrictions.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
